description: Works to trees in the Enfield Town Conservation Area: (T50) evergreen oak - dismantle and fell to ground level; (G4) ash - dismantle and fell to ground level; (T8) sycamore - dismantle and fell to ground level; (T9) yew - deadwood crown; (T51) thuja - dismantle and fell to ground level; (T52) lime - reduce crown by 4m; (T53) sycamore - reduce crown by 2.5m; (T55) evergreen oak - trees overhanging cricket nets, trim overhang by 2m  (T54) horse chestnut - reduce by 4m and clear brash on floor around tree; (T12) sycamore - fell; (T15) cedar - remove broken limb from within crown of tree.
